kroopt vendors a portable-C subset of HACL* (the High-Assurance Cryptographic
Library, part of Project Everest) under `Kroopt/Native/hacl/`, together with the
KaRaMeL/kremlin runtime headers it requires. These files are redistributed
verbatim with their upstream license headers retained:

  - the HACL* generated C (Hacl_*.c/.h, Lib_Memzero0.c, internal/ headers) is
    under the MIT License, Copyright (c) 2016-2020 INRIA, CMU and Microsoft
    Corporation;
  - the KaRaMeL/kremlin headers (include/kremlin/**, minimal/*.h) are under the
    Apache License, Version 2.0, Copyright (c) INRIA and Microsoft Corporation.

Both licenses are permissive and compatible with kroopt's own Apache-2.0
license. The full third-party license texts are in
`Kroopt/Native/hacl/LICENSE`, and a provenance summary (upstream, version 0.4.5,
the exact subset, and the no-modifications statement) is in the repository-root
`THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md`.

Upstream: https://github.com/hacl-star/hacl-star (obtained via the `hacl-star`
OCaml package, v0.4.5). The vendored subset covers exactly the primitives the
`TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256` cipher suite needs with X25519 and Ed25519:
SHA-256/384, X25519, ChaCha20-Poly1305, HKDF/HMAC-SHA256, and Ed25519. No vale
assembly and no EverCrypt dispatch layer are included. kroopt's own glue
(`Kroopt/Native/kroopt_ffi.c`, Apache-2.0) and Lean wrappers only marshal byte
buffers across the FFI and add no cryptographic logic.

The `iotakt` byte-transport dependency is integrated through an abstract
transport interface (`Kroopt.Conn.Transport`); iotakt is one possible instance
and is not bundled here.
